@j-funk that would work if subsequent tests didn't rely on setUp creating a fresh new state with every call. If we decorate `setUp`, the cassette created will works with `test_case1`, but then if it gets used while recording `test_case2` it won't work because `test_case2` expects that `setUp` would have created a fresh user. 

```
class Example(TestCase):
    @vcr.use_cassette()
    def setUp(self):
        # Network requests to create a user here
    @vcr.use_cassette()
    def test_case1(self):
        # Other things, other requests expecting a fresh user 1
    @vcr.use_cassette()
    def test_case2(self):
        # Other things, other requests expecting a fresh user 2
```

We're specifically using vcr to mock out Stripe, in case you were wondering. Thanks for the great library 💯

