How can we handle when a device/child gets reset/rebooted? It starts from zero sequence number but its previous sequence number is remembered by all the neighbors/parent in the network and I guess they may reject new frames from the device after reset when checking the sequence number.

With regards to security MLE and MAC frame counters, we save them in flash/settings with a jump ahead increase `OPENTHREAD_CONFIG_STORE_FRAME_COUNTER_AHEAD` to ensure that on a reset we start after the previous counter value. They are `uint32` and never wrap around.

