I think one problem with the current mechanism is that doesn't work well for long-running programs.

We have a use case where the driver simply pulls up a bunch of long-running actors and then the actors just work on their own (sometimes indefinitely). However, because the lifecycle of the actors are bound to the driver, the driver has to be sleeping there without doing anything. Moreover, if the driver accidentally dies, the whole system may go down as well. 

If we have job management, a more natural process will be:
1) user submits a job and gets a job id;
2) driver pulls up actors and exits soon;
3) user can cancel the job at any point through a web portal

